o, Primo.","Italian: patronymic or plural form of   Casale  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Casale","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Antonio, Carmine, Rocco, Salvatore, Concetta, Domenic, Pasquale, Aldo, Carlo, Domenico, Gennaro.","Italian: from Late Latin <i>casale</i> ‘hut, cottage’, a diminutive of <i>casa</i> ‘house’, hence a topographic name for someone who lived in such a dwelling or a habitational name from any of the various places called with this word, in particular a place in Piedmont."]}]},{"name":"Countess","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Nottinghamshire, of Norman origin): from Middle English <i>contas(e)</i>, Old French <i>contesse</i> ‘countess’, applied as a nickname for a proud, haughty woman or for a foppish man, or as an occupational name for a servant of a countess."],"variants":[{"name":"Countiss","meanings":["English: variant of   Countess  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Countess Casati was born in 1203, in Novara, Piedmont, Italy. She married Ubertus Pirovano in 1223, in Invorio Inferiore, Novara, Piedmont, Italy. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1247, in Invorio, Novara, Piedmont, Italy, at the age of 44."},"et":{"1203–1247":"1203–1247","1198–1226":"1198–1226","1226–1276":"1226–1276","1226":"1226","1203":"1203","1247":"1247","1223":"1223","1276":"1276","1198":"1198","Invorio, Novara, Piemonte, Itália":"Invorio, Novara, Piemonte, Itaalia","Novara, Italia":"Novara, Piemonte, Itaalia","Invorio Inferiore, Novara, Piemonte, Itália":"Invorio Inferiore, Novara, Piemonte, Itaalia","Invorio, Piemonte IT":"Invorio, Novara, Piemonte, Itaalia","Invorio Inferiore, Invorio, Novara, Piedmont, Italy":"Invorio Inferiore, Novara, Piemonte, Itaalia"},"fi":{"1203–1247":"1203–1247","1198–1226":"1198–1226","1226–1276":"1226–1276","1226":"1226","1203":"1203","1247":"1247","1223":"1223","1276":"1276","1198":"1198","Invorio, Novara, Piemonte, Itá